dcterms:creator: Ali Borji
dcterms:description: The MNIST dataset consists of handwritten digits and is commonly used for training various image processing systems. In this paper, it is used to evaluate the effectiveness of the proposed NKE attack on deep neural networks.
dcterms:title: MNIST

dcterms:creator: Ali Borji
dcterms:description: The CIFAR-10 dataset contains 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is used in this paper to assess the performance of the NKE attack on deep neural networks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10
